<br>
'tanking' a tank is a very bad idea, but what happens is if you are able to get a little distance between you and the tank then you'll have room to try to cast and channel.<br>
<br>
Then the idea is just like a wizard to shadowstep and re skin up if it wears off. Be aware that while you do this chances aer the melee is pumicing off your dots. That's why with a necro I think against a melee open up with a nice pyrocuror (or ignite blood) channel a splurt, either the melee decides to stay there to pumice your dots in which case you can stick pet on him and recast the dots while he pumices, or he chases you and he is taking damage.<br>
<br>
Necros are really good since they have skin spells, shadowstep and also heal spells that you can use on a passing by lvl 1 mob. I play a necro also on RZ and I find they are better than wizards by an enormous margin, unless you want to sit at portals and gank people before they get control.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utrylun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trylun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/27/02 3:18:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Aurore, any decent Wizard will blow a Necro away.<br>
